text.*:
The Federal Standard 595 camouflage colours were developed by the Mobility Equipment Research and Design Command (M.E.R.D.C) during the 1970s.[1] The colours and pattern scheme could be adjusted as the environments changed.[1] Military modelers often use the Federal Standard 595 colours for painting models and soldiers.[1]

Camouflage colours[edit]

To be included in the list the colour must be "Federal Standard 595" and have the word "camouflage" in it.
